This paper is primarily focused on fairness in recommender systems, which is a topic that falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of metrics and algorithms, which are common topics in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper touches on social implications of recommendation algorithms, which could fall under the social and information sciences (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also discusses bias and calibration, which could fall under the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses real-world datasets, which could fall under the social computing (cs.SOC) sub-category.
